Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.52,0:00:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.19,0:00:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.06,0:00:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for spending part of your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.37,0:00:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,WWDC with us, talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching with Swift Playgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.57,0:00:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My name's Bill Dudney, I'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,joined shortly by my colleague,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.47,0:00:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth, to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.77,0:00:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching with Swift Playgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.39,0:00:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you might have noticed, over
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.91,0:00:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the last few years we started
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.55,0:00:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with Hour of Code, and even some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.12,0:00:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,initiatives before that, that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole world is now talking
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about people learning about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.61,0:00:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,computational thinking, about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.42,0:00:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how to program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.77,0:00:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In India, in Asia, and Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.90,0:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's big school systems like
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.28,0:01:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,New York and Chicago talking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about teaching all of their kids
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.35,0:01:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,how to code.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.78,0:01:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even heffalumps are learning how
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.36,0:01:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to code.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.15,0:01:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere, everybody is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.86,0:01:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,learning how to code.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.63,0:01:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And, we are really excited about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.54,0:01:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.84,0:01:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's such a fantastic time to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.15,0:01:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in a place where, to be in a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.43,0:01:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,time, where everyone is starting
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.75,0:01:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about coding.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.75,0:01:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, our talk today is divided
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.96,0:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,into two major sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.48,0:01:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one, I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.29,0:01:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,cover, talking about teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.82,0:01:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then Elizabeth is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about designing and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.17,0:01:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing playgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.10,0:01:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But, those two sections have
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.45,0:01:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,three main pillars in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.95,0:01:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Goal, passion, and audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.69,0:01:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's get started with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.61,0:01:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching, and specifically about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.59,0:01:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.61,0:01:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as a teacher, you of course
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.64,0:01:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have to have a goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.59,0:01:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What information is it that you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,want to impart to your learners.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.27,0:01:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But, equally important, is your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.92,0:01:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,learner's goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.21,0:01:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that your learner is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.50,0:01:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get out of that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.45,0:01:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,content?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They need their goal to be front
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and center of the content so
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.77,0:02:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that they stay motivated,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.37,0:02:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because while learning to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.28,0:02:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,program is not hard, it does
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,take hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.15,0:02:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a place where I'm sure many
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.99,0:02:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of us have been with mathematics
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.57,0:02:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is to either love it, or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.23,0:02:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm sure we all have friends
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.59,0:02:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.52,0:02:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As programmers, probably most of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.12,0:02:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,us are into mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.45,0:02:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We've at least played with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and done some stuff with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.38,0:02:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who don't get it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.63,0:02:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,though, are often, or who aren't
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.30,0:02:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,excited by mathematics are often
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.80,0:02:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,turned off by it, by some
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.32,0:02:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,experience where they end up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.56,0:02:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with this long list of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.13,0:02:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.06,0:02:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Polynomials, trig, exponentials,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.17,0:02:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithms, their inverses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.17,0:02:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Solving for "x."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember, when I was younger,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.34,0:02:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and sitting in my geometry class
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with my teacher, Mr. Carlin, I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.26,0:02:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,would ask him, probably once a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.25,0:02:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,week, I was a real pest, "When
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.27,0:02:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,am I ever going to use this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.47,0:03:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And, he would look at me and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.57,0:03:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Please stop asking me that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.61,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,question."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.50,0:03:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And, eventually, after I've
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pestered him enough, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.81,0:03:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"Look, you're probably never
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.51,0:03:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,going to use this, but it's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,really cool anyway," and that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.80,0:03:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of flipped a bit in my head
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.40,0:03:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to go from looking at math as
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.28,0:03:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,utilitarian, to looking at math
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as something that's beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and fun to mess with, like a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,puzzle to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.41,0:03:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, that really struck me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.11,0:03:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and it turned my direction away
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from being frustrated with not
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.77,0:03:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,having some practical
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.80,0:03:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,application for it, to enjoying
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.97,0:03:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it just to solve puzzles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.50,0:03:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, little did Mr.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Carlin know, that I would
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually become a nerd, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.63,0:03:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,deal with geometry all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so thank you, Mr. Carlin, for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.53,0:03:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching me geometry despite my
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.16,0:03:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.52,0:03:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.61,0:03:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have a couple of examples
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.78,0:03:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that I use to try to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.40,0:03:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,this concept to people, because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's so important that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.38,0:03:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we think through this, when
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:03:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we're thinking about teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.35,0:04:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, imagine you're trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.58,0:04:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to do art.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead of being artistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.79,0:04:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and spreading paint around a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.16,0:04:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,canvas, instead, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.70,0:04:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraged, or forced, to study
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.41,0:04:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the texture of colors, or the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.14,0:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,look of the color, or the shape
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.98,0:04:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the brush, but never able to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.01,0:04:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,apply that paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.22,0:04:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be really hard to stay
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.73,0:04:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,focused on learning to become an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.39,0:04:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,artist when you can't do art.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.62,0:04:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to create, they want
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.73,0:04:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to build things, or they want to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,make things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And, if you had to study that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.99,0:04:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be very difficult to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,get through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So much better to let people,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're learning to paint
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a mess, smear the paint
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.34,0:04:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the place without
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,concern, really, for what it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.28,0:04:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.02,0:04:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can worry about that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing with music.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.19,0:04:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine if you had to know what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.65,0:04:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,every dot, every line, every arc
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.07,0:04:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,on this diagram meant before you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.21,0:04:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,could pick up a guitar, or start
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.91,0:04:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,playing with your piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.90,0:04:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be very difficult to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.17,0:04:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,get through all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.74,0:05:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I encourage people who are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.61,0:05:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about teaching to start
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.14,0:05:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That question is what drives the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.11,0:05:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,learner's goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.40,0:05:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,From that question, the learner
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.99,0:05:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,drives internal motivation to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve the hard work of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.99,0:05:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,learning the material you're
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.92,0:05:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get across.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.87,0:05:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings us next, to the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so important that we as
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,teachers think through the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.76,0:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,audience that we're aiming to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.54,0:05:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.39,0:05:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they brand new coders?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they understand anything with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.39,0:05:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,coding?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.07,0:05:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, are they moderately
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced and they're trying
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.53,0:05:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to gain more insight into some
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.10,0:05:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,particular piece of material?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.82,0:05:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to know who your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.92,0:05:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,audience is and then make your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,content communicate to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.54,0:05:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What I often see happening is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.03,0:05:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people taking syntax and other
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,things from a computer science
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.06,0:05:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,degree in college and then sort
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of moving it down to a level so
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,younger people can understand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.80,0:05:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you end up with this huge
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud of concepts that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:05:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to get down, all these syntax
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.98,0:05:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,items.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.76,0:06:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, it's very
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,important that you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.01,0:06:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,syntax, you can't code without
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.52,0:06:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing what syntax is, so in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.53,0:06:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to Code, the way we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,approach that, is that we build
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.42,0:06:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this engaging world with these
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.02,0:06:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,great characters and these silly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.71,0:06:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,animations, and beautiful audio
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.31,0:06:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to engage the learner so that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll go through the hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.05,0:06:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of learning what a for loop is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.93,0:06:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an example of one puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.28,0:06:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have that takes Byte
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,around the four sides of this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:06:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,world, picking up gems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.73,0:06:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to do that, you of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.04,0:06:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,course use a for loop, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.34,0:06:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,have that stated at the top of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.90,0:06:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the page, but that's not the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.65,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The learner's goal is to pick up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.73,0:06:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,these items and to solve the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.22,0:06:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, we use that goal to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.55,0:06:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,drive an internal motivation to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,go and learn what a for loop is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.27,0:06:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The next step is often to dive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,into something like algorithms
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and data structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.89,0:06:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I love all these algorithms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.56,0:06:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Half of these names, I looked
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought, Hmm, I wonder what
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:06:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, and I almost got
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.37,0:06:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,distracted from prepping my
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.57,0:07:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,slides by digging into what is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.00,0:07:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Soundex.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.52,0:07:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.55,0:07:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many of you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.79,0:07:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have interacted with younger
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,people, but I doubt very
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.63,0:07:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,seriously-- well, many of you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,are much younger than me, I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.34,0:07:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,know, but I'm talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.32,0:07:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,young learners in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of them have come to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.01,0:07:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you with a bucket of integers
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and said, "You know, I really
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.12,0:07:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,wish you would help me sort
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,these."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.56,0:07:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.06,0:07:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No one wants to learn about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.92,0:07:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sorting, they have a goal and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.63,0:07:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,sorting will help them achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.97,0:07:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that goal, so you want to focus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.23,0:07:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,on the audience's goals and then
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.25,0:07:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,help them achieve those goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.63,0:07:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again back here to Learn to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Code, when we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,algorithmic learning and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.58,0:07:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,computational thinking, or when
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.33,0:07:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we're thinking about using those
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,concepts to teach people, we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,build this content like this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,same simple puzzle that we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.47,0:07:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier, that's drawing the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.85,0:07:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,learner in to thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.54,0:07:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what an algorithm is, without
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:07:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,even using the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.12,0:08:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, later when we get close to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of Learn to Code 1, we
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.12,0:08:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,approach this puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.45,0:08:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This puzzle is a challenge page
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.74,0:08:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and says to the learner, Hey, go
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.61,0:08:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Solve this in any way that you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.63,0:08:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,want to in the most efficient
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.52,0:08:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,way that you see possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.59,0:08:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But, this is after a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.48,0:08:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of solving these puzzles where
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they start to understand and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.41,0:08:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,think algorithmically, so they
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.05,0:08:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this and think, Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.35,0:08:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's two diamonds, or there's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.69,0:08:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,two gems, and there's two things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to flip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.35,0:08:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that's just programming the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.06,0:08:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,easy parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, when I started
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.90,0:08:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,programming, I would not have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.60,0:08:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,built the WWDC app, properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have made a table
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller and a cell and a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.14,0:08:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,model.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.65,0:08:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just dump all the code
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.97,0:08:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,into the view controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.50,0:08:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because I read MVC when I first
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,got started, and I had no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what that meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.43,0:08:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Modeling is difficult, the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.74,0:08:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,syntax and the algorithms, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so forth are the straightforward
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.53,0:08:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,part.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:08:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, another thing that I notice
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.25,0:08:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that people get bogged down in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.93,0:08:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.87,0:09:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching this stuff is, to focus
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.90,0:09:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on details.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.07,0:09:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.21,0:09:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they're really important.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Several years ago, I thought, I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.74,0:09:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,really want to learn to do 3D
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,programming.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.20,0:09:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always thought it's really
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,cool, I love how fast it is, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.77,0:09:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the parallel nature of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.43,0:09:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I started diving into Open
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.84,0:09:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,GL.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Bought a couple of books, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.73,0:09:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,without question, every one of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.28,0:09:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,those books had this diagram in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to give you a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.34,0:09:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of seconds to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.60,0:09:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.29,0:09:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Study it hard, there'll be a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.39,0:09:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,test.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.60,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here's a picture of a dog
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.43,0:09:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,playing with a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.19,0:09:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one did you get more out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.02,0:09:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughter ]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.11,0:09:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're first getting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.97,0:09:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,started with 3D graphics,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.51,0:09:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at this diagram, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:09:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,very hard to make heads or tails
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.56,0:09:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of it, you might as well be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.38,0:09:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at a picture of a puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, what we want to do, is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.51,0:10:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,3D graphics is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.02,0:10:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were teaching 3D graphics,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I would start with fun stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,like Byte doing his silly dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.41,0:10:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.95,0:10:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He's fantastic, this is so
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.60,0:10:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, everything in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.92,0:10:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that diagram-- vertex shaders
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.37,0:10:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and primitive processing and so
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.42,0:10:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,forth-- all of that is really
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,important to getting every
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.95,0:10:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,single frame that you see happen
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.53,0:10:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on the screen, onto the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.40,0:10:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you never want to start
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to start with fun stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to get people motivated instead
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.85,0:10:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of bogging them down in details.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.98,0:10:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.35,0:10:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You, as a teacher, as a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.50,0:10:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,developer, have passion for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,particular things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You love some piece of computer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics, or you love to think
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.53,0:10:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,about UIKit, or ARKit, or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.31,0:10:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever, and you want to teach
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.02,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.73,0:11:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring that passion in to how you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.85,0:11:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,approach the teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to light the fire of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.75,0:11:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that passion in the people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.15,0:11:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to reach because
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.38,0:11:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what will give them the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.33,0:11:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,internal motivation to do the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.71,0:11:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,hard work to learn what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.29,0:11:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to get across to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.42,0:11:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.74,0:11:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, teaching with Swift
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Playgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on goal, audience, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.20,0:11:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.26,0:11:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that's teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.10,0:11:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to invite Elizabeth
