Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.05,0:13:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to dive right in there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn how to code in Byte's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.66,0:13:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's colorful, it's exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where the learner's code
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.08,0:13:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to execute, where
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to see what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.42,0:13:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they've created.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.62,0:13:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your point, to get them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.17,0:13:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.64,0:13:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to teach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.12,0:13:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to these collection
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.51,0:13:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of pages that make up a Swift
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.02,0:13:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Playground, there are a few
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,other features that you can add
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.61,0:13:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to make your experiences really
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,gripping.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.23,0:13:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the first ones is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.82,0:13:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutscenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.90,0:13:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're familiar with the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.78,0:13:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to Codes, then you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,probably have seen some of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.21,0:13:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,these.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.25,0:13:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We typically add them at the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.58,0:13:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning of new chapters, or
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.06,0:13:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,new sections, to introduce a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.94,0:13:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,concept in a fun, animated way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These are written in HTML, and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.96,0:14:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they're a good way to introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.41,0:14:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a new topic before you dive
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,straight into the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.45,0:14:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Give the learner a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.29,0:14:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is they're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.39,0:14:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also add hints to your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.50,0:14:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,playground books.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,These are so important for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.27,0:14:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,giving the learner a contextual
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of where they're going
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.32,0:14:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do a bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.26,0:14:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,introspecting on the learner's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.58,0:14:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,code in order to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.33,0:14:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what mistake they might
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,have made, and offer them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.35,0:14:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,tailored help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.63,0:14:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredibly engaging to have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.22,0:14:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,software understand what you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.92,0:14:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,need specifically instead of a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.66,0:14:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one size fits all sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.40,0:14:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, use hints.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing to keep in mind with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,hints is that some learners
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,really don't like the extra
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.63,0:14:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,help, they want to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't put essential
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,information to solving the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.25,0:14:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,problem in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.40,0:14:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Make these real hints for those
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.61,0:14:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If hints aren't enough, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.59,0:14:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,also add solutions to your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.28,0:14:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,playground pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,These are essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.56,0:15:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the first time you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.76,0:15:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were trying to learn a new
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.64,0:15:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you do it just with
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,someone explaining conceptually?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.20,0:15:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, did you need to look at a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.18,0:15:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,reference example?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.18,0:15:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,These are so helpful for your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,learners that get stuck and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.08,0:15:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't sure of the syntax,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.41,0:15:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't sure how to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.04,0:15:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The solution gives them that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.66,0:15:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,help they need.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise they might get
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.68,0:15:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,frustrated and leave your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.92,0:15:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,playground book entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.68,0:15:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also add assessments at
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.71,0:15:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.82,0:15:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,These typically pop up once the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.69,0:15:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,learner has completed the task
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've set them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.55,0:15:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also customize these
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.37,0:15:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on how your learner
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.93,0:15:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,has solved the puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.42,0:15:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you wanted them to use for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.99,0:15:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,loops, but they used repeated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.44,0:15:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,code instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's your chance to suggest to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.35,0:15:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,them, great job, you completed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.25,0:15:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the puzzle, but maybe next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.43,0:15:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,use a for loop instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit better of a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.31,0:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.29,0:15:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. So we're all set,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.29,0:15:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We know about pages, we know
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.89,0:16:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,about assessments and hints,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.82,0:16:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coding time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so. We went ahead to the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.32,0:16:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,drawing board.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These are some of my actual
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.67,0:16:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,notes in the actual notebook
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.40,0:16:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that I keep when I'm designing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.09,0:16:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for Swift Playgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick sketches, just getting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.68,0:16:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts out of my brain onto
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.38,0:16:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I might have a thought while I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.98,0:16:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,riding the shuttle, or in the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.65,0:16:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,shower, and I just want to get
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.05,0:16:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that down somewhere so that I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.28,0:16:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,can iterate on it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.45,0:16:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting out writing code, is a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,really expensive way to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You might spend weeks getting a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,cool working demo ready, and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then show it to a potential
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.48,0:16:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,learner, and they are totally
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.27,0:16:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,lost, or they think it's boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.53,0:16:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now you're stuck and you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.79,0:16:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,have to redo all of those weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.69,0:16:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of coding work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.10,0:16:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, start with cheap
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.81,0:16:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,prototyping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.05,0:16:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as easy to show a set
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of storyboards on a whiteboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.84,0:16:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or in a KeyNote even, to some
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.27,0:16:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,potential learners, to some of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.58,0:17:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your colleagues to get feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in that initial stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all set now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.11,0:17:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got the main parts of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,playground book in mind, we
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.00,0:17:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,understand we want to start out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.11,0:17:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with cheap, fast prototyping, so
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,now let's take those ideals that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.34,0:17:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill taught us about, and put
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.41,0:17:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,them into practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the learner's goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.12,0:17:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take a minute here to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.13,0:17:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,help you separate in your minds
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual different goals that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.51,0:17:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.95,0:17:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's your goal as the author.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.02,0:17:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want your learner to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.15,0:17:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,get out of the whole playground,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.94,0:17:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and of each individual page?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.68,0:17:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are separate goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.67,0:17:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Your learner, as well, has a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.35,0:17:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,goal on a per-page basis, and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the whole playground
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.53,0:17:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in Cipher, a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.05,0:17:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,cryptography-focused playground,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we released recently, the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,learner's goal is to solve the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,mystery over the course of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.33,0:17:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They find this encrypted note
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.50,0:17:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and want to figure out what it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.51,0:17:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,means.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.74,0:18:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My goal as the author is to get
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.75,0:18:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,them interested in cryptography
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.48,0:18:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and give them a few new words,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,plain text, ciphertext, just to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.09,0:18:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,spark that interest in a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.53,0:18:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,potential discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.50,0:18:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, keep those goals in mind and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,figure out how you can make them
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.26,0:18:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,intermarry in the best way, to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.16,0:18:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,fully support your learner in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.50,0:18:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,their experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.75,0:18:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, let's walk through some
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,potential goals that you might
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have, and that we often use in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.52,0:18:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift Playgrounds on each page.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.55,0:18:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Completing a task.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's probably the most
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.32,0:18:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar to a lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.09,0:18:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We use this a lot in the Learn
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.34,0:18:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to Codes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.37,0:18:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Collect all the gems, flip two
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,switches, and collect one gem,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.86,0:18:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,place the expert in the right
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.09,0:18:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,area.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.17,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These are easy for the learner
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand what you want them
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.88,0:18:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.73,0:18:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a clear starting
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.78,0:18:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,point, a clear ending point, and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.99,0:18:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,these are easy for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.04,0:18:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,assess, and offer that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.57,0:18:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,personalized-- those
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.51,0:18:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,personalized hints and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.20,0:18:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,assessments at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.10,0:18:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.51,0:19:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I love these kind of pages,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.94,0:19:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because I like to play around
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with the code I'm given.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,These are a really good way to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.60,0:19:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,introduce learners to something
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.32,0:19:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,complex, to give them a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.51,0:19:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where they're going before they
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.42,0:19:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,dive in to the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We often use this by showing a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.57,0:19:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,whole big block of code, maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.89,0:19:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,new functions the learner hasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.41,0:19:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,seen yet, maybe new variables,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,even new concepts, and then we
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,minimize the amount of code
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.80,0:19:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that's actually editable to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.22,0:19:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,them, so they're not overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.87,0:19:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by seeing, whoa, this is a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of new stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.77,0:19:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, they can pick out the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.57,0:19:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"I know how to change a color, I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.70,0:19:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,know how to change a radius to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.37,0:19:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,negative."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.65,0:19:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And, they can experiment, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.93,0:19:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,have fun with this thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.31,0:19:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they're about to dive more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,deeply into.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.38,0:19:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Practicing a new skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.04,0:19:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping you all practice a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.82,0:19:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,new skill right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.51,0:19:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill taught us about goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.59,0:19:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,audience, and passion, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.00,0:19:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reiterating that to you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.43,0:19:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that hopefully when you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.39,0:19:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,leave this room, you have those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.23,0:20:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,three concepts in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Learners won't grok a concept
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately, the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.64,0:20:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You might wish they would, but
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.99,0:20:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure through experience;
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.32,0:20:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,think back to when you first
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.50,0:20:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,learned a new, complicated
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.57,0:20:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you have written a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.29,0:20:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,definition, explained it to one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.89,0:20:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of your colleagues immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.73,0:20:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you needed to practice that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.47,0:20:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,skill, to use it in different
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.07,0:20:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,contexts so that you can then go
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.38,0:20:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and apply that to some new
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.90,0:20:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.46,0:20:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, really important to include
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,these types of pages in your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.23,0:20:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,playground book.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.92,0:20:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.90,0:20:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is sort of different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.96,0:20:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk a lot about code and the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.64,0:20:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,learner code on each page, but
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.57,0:20:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,often in the Learn to Codes and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.18,0:20:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the challenges in all of your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.54,0:20:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,playground books, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.65,0:20:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,introducing something totally
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.62,0:20:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,new.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.52,0:20:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the cryptography playground,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.02,0:20:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm introducing all of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.53,0:20:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,cryptography, and there's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated words like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.09,0:20:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,ciphertext and key and message.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.62,0:20:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of new information
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.28,0:20:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for a learner to take in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.27,0:20:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you want to make sure you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.26,0:21:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,give them that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.89,0:21:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To read, understand, and reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.44,0:21:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,on what you're telling them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.36,0:21:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We have several pages that don't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.87,0:21:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,have any user coding on a page,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.03,0:21:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because those pages are
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,concept-heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.70,0:21:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, we want to give the learner
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.98,0:21:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.46,0:21:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, create.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.34,0:21:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,These pages are awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where you really get to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.23,0:21:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,show your skills, show what
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.83,0:21:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you've learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We've given you, the author, all
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.13,0:21:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the tools you need, and now the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.43,0:21:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,learner is able to go nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.25,0:21:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They know how to change colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.53,0:21:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they know how to add functions,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.30,0:21:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they can make the robot dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but they couldn't before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.42,0:21:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is their chance to really
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.57,0:21:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,explore, and to feel empowered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.66,0:21:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why they came to coding.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.60,0:21:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you all come to coding?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.31,0:21:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.18,0:21:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,To create something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.81,0:21:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that in mind, that that's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.18,0:21:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,likely what's in your learners'
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.40,0:21:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,minds too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.31,0:21:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That they want to create
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.22,0:21:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.11,0:21:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, give them that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.01,0:21:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.45,0:21:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Include a wide variety of these
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.46,0:22:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,types of pages in your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.68,0:22:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,playgrounds, and you'll keep
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.13,0:22:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your learners engaged,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.54,0:22:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,interested, and excited for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.94,0:22:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what's coming next.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.12,0:22:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how do we do all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.94,0:22:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we get the learner to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.23,0:22:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,these places?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.94,0:22:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How to create these pages?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.16,0:22:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in Swift Playgrounds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.30,0:22:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, you have several prose
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.12,0:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,tools available to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.60,0:22:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one is glossary entries.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.96,0:22:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,These are incredibly important
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.57,0:22:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.01,0:22:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,your audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.47,0:22:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one of those big,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.46,0:22:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,important points.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.21,0:22:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Algorithm might be a simple word
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.52,0:22:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of you, many of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.66,0:22:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're coders, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.71,0:22:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,programmers, you've been around
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.42,0:22:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the block, and you know what an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.59,0:22:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,algorithm is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.08,0:22:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But, a beginner, who's brand new
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.71,0:22:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to coding, that's a difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.26,0:22:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,word.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.08,0:22:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Something they can't just intuit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.63,0:22:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from reading the rest of your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.65,0:22:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,prose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.58,0:22:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, offering this glossary
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.02,0:22:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,entry, which is triggered in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.69,0:22:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift Playgrounds just by
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.87,0:22:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,tapping on that differently
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.03,0:22:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,colored word, gives them the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.76,0:23:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,support they need to keep on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.81,0:23:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with your playground book.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.84,0:23:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind, you, as the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.49,0:23:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,author, are not going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.97,0:23:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there to pop out of the page,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.39,0:23:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell your learner something
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.96,0:23:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're having trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.31,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to communicate solely
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.00,0:23:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,via the medium of text.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.92,0:23:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you want to use all the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.14,0:23:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tools at your disposal to give
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.81,0:23:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,extra help where it's needed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.69,0:23:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and support your learner in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.54,0:23:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,their process.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.99,0:23:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A great way to figure out what
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.82,0:23:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,kinds of glossary entries you're
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.44,0:23:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,going to need is by user
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.20,0:23:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.31,0:23:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Put this in the prototyping
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.78,0:23:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,stage when you get some prose
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.19,0:23:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,written down in front of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.41,0:23:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,learners, and listen to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.75,0:23:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What words don't they
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.57,0:23:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.55,0:23:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What concept did they clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.85,0:23:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not get because they skipped
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,over a vocab word?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.58,0:23:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, include these in your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.71,0:23:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,glossary entries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.96,0:23:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also worth noting, that, if
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.44,0:23:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you're localizing your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.30,0:23:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,playground, you can add
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.76,0:23:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,additional glossary entries in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.35,0:23:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,different localized languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.34,0:23:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that if there's something
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.69,0:23:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,jargon-y that maybe an English
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.23,0:23:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,speaker would understand, you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.68,0:23:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,can offer a glossary entry to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.40,0:24:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that in another language.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.59,0:24:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.95,0:24:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a minute to read this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.32,0:24:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.55,0:24:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You all feel confident about
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.95,0:24:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,substitution ciphers?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.41,0:24:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You could send me a message
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.42,0:24:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,right now in substitution cipher
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.13,0:24:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with a shift of 3?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.62,0:24:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What about if I also gave you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.33,0:24:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this diagram?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.50,0:24:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is much more valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.87,0:24:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's helpful to have both,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.23,0:24:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.11,0:24:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The diagram on its own wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.42,0:24:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,do it, but just the prose
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.31,0:24:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,without this visual, impactful
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.62,0:24:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is not going to cut it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.20,0:24:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so helpful to have visual
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.54,0:24:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,aids in explaining difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.15,0:24:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.45,0:24:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Do keep in mind, that if you add
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.18,0:24:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,visual aids, which you can add
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.78,0:24:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in that prose section, right in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.66,0:24:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the prose, that you want to make
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.06,0:24:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,sure they have accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.45,0:24:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,labels, so that your users using
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.53,0:24:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver have just as rich of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.22,0:25:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,an experience as those who are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.05,0:25:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,not using VoiceOver.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.20,0:25:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a wall of text.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.52,0:25:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of stuff going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.80,0:25:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, there's a callout.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.39,0:25:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I know which part of this I need
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.73,0:25:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay attention to.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.91,0:25:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here, new awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.29,0:25:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,function.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.18,0:25:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.92,0:25:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In a lot of our user testing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,users, no matter what age group,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.43,0:25:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what experience level, often
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.34,0:25:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,skim the prose.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.79,0:25:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to get right into
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.87,0:25:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,coding, they don't care about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.77,0:25:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all the awesome instructions
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.21,0:25:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you've given, you've slaved over
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.65,0:25:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.70,0:25:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They just want to get in there
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.99,0:25:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and write some code.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.09,0:25:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, support that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.66,0:25:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Give people their tl;dr, too
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.99,0:25:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,long; didn't read it version, in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.40,0:25:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the middle so they can get right
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.01,0:25:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.63,0:25:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, offer them that prose
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.47,0:25:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,support, around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.10,0:25:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If your learner does dive right
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.55,0:25:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in, tries out new awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.65,0:25:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,function, and it doesn't do what
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.10,0:25:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they expected, they need to be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.04,0:25:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,able to come back and read about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.08,0:25:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and find out what it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.84,0:26:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all about supporting your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.02,0:26:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,learner in every aspect you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.62,0:26:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,think they might need support.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.66,0:26:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the shortcut bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.28,0:26:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This might not seem like a prose
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.00,0:26:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,tool, but it's incredibly
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.25,0:26:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,important.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.16,0:26:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, as the authors, have
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.72,0:26:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,control over what appears in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.46,0:26:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this shortcut bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.15,0:26:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how your learner is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.34,0:26:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,going to start coding.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.75,0:26:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how they're doing it on
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.80,0:26:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,an iPad.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.74,0:26:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Tapping functions, tapping
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.88,0:26:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,keywords.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.10,0:26:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is their main toolbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.84,0:26:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, make it easy to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.37,0:26:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Only include relevant choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.55,0:26:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If your learner's on page tw0 of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.17,0:26:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,your playground book, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.62,0:26:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,have functions from page six and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.69,0:26:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,seven in that shortcut bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.82,0:26:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to be exhausting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.12,0:26:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and distracting.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.70,0:26:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to have to scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.96,0:26:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,through, finally get to the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.83,0:26:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,functions they wanted for this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.94,0:26:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,page, and wonder why they had
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.48,0:26:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all these extra functions in the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.61,0:26:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.69,0:26:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It might even be confusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.53,0:26:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they thought they needed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.60,0:26:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to use those other functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.16,0:27:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But, they don't, and now they're
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.19,0:27:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.92,0:27:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you haven't gotten your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.73,0:27:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,point across as well as you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.07,0:27:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,might have.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.77,0:27:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Use concise method names.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.76,0:27:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This one can be a little tough,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.46,0:27:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because sometimes the method's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.14,0:27:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,got to say what it's got to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.94,0:27:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.68,0:27:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I have here, "shift word
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.79,0:27:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by," easy, fits on the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.87,0:27:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's easy for the learner to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.89,0:27:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.37,0:27:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Important to keep your audience
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.71,0:27:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind here too, in terms of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.23,0:27:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of vocabulary you're
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.81,0:27:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,using in these method names.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.64,0:27:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Your word choice is just as
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.93,0:27:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,important as the concepts you're
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.45,0:27:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,leading them through.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.80,0:27:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And, finally, please provide
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.26,0:27:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,common keywords.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.23,0:27:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We all love autocomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.57,0:27:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your learner will love it if
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.71,0:27:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they can just tap "func", tap
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.74,0:27:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"var", tap "if" to put it in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.32,0:27:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.14,0:27:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make them type those over
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.72,0:27:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.62,0:27:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to focus on the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.50,0:27:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,learning, and one of the most
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.67,0:27:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,important things about focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.35,0:27:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,on the learning is not having
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.36,0:27:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ancillary busyness going on in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.88,0:28:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind of remembering, was it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.59,0:28:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"func" with a capital F, does
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.37,0:28:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the "var"-- do I need a space
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.82,0:28:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,before and after the equals?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.73,0:28:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.61,0:28:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to have to deal
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.77,0:28:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with that, and your learner
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.62,0:28:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.80,0:28:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just provide these helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.84,0:28:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,things in the shortcut bar, and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.77,0:28:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,your learner will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.75,0:28:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on what you really want to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.25,0:28:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,teach them, and that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.39,0:28:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.30,0:28:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've talked about the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.48,0:28:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,learner, a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.51,0:28:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that brings us to the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.16,0:28:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,second overarching point.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.26,0:28:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is your learner?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.15,0:28:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they a beginner?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.69,0:28:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they advanced?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.40,0:28:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you writing a computational
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.76,0:28:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,biology playground, and showing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.57,0:28:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it to biologists?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.93,0:28:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, showing it to computer
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.90,0:28:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,scientists?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.29,0:28:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people are going to bring
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.62,0:28:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,totally different backgrounds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.15,0:28:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.58,0:28:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you really need to get to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.67,0:28:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,know your learner and understand
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.50,0:28:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where they're coming from to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.86,0:28:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,provide them the best, richest,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.02,0:28:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,most supportive learning
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.06,0:28:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.36,0:28:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to walk you through
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.39,0:28:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,some examples now, of pages from
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.60,0:28:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,our playground books where we
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.38,0:29:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,had goals in mind, but we also
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.30,0:29:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,had to keep our audience
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.58,0:29:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,strongly in the forefront.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.88,0:29:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a page from Learn to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.63,0:29:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Code 3, where we're asking the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.72,0:29:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,learner to add a background
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.24,0:29:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,image to the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.92,0:29:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We say it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.73,0:29:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Set a background image.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.01,0:29:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Add it to the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.88,0:29:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that's because this is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.95,0:29:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,targeted at a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.81,0:29:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Complete a task-style goal, like
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.85,0:29:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked about from before, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.40,0:29:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,beginner audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.41,0:29:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Set a background image, alright,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.30,0:29:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm primed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.27,0:29:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, right here, this is how
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.35,0:29:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.09,0:29:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,scene.backgroundImage equals
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.57,0:29:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"image literal."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.61,0:29:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I give the learner the syntax,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.69,0:29:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because, again, this is targeted
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.95,0:29:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,at a beginner who's not going to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.61,0:29:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have all that far-reaching
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.20,0:29:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,computer science knowledge, not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.97,0:29:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even that far-reaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.11,0:29:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,To us, this seems simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.37,0:29:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.24,0:29:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"backgroundImage" is the name of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.70,0:29:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that property.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.83,0:29:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But a beginner doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.33,0:29:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And since we're all content
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.53,0:29:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,matter experts, it's really hard
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.53,0:29:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to put ourselves in the shoes of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.30,0:29:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a beginner who isn't familiar
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.95,0:30:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with the syntax.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.48,0:30:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why user testing is so
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.00,0:30:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,important.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.76,0:30:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To figure out what kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.80,0:30:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,logical leaps you're making,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.82,0:30:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that your learner needs to be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.04,0:30:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,walked through a little more
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.42,0:30:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.52,0:30:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We then give them extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.28,0:30:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,explicit instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.11,0:30:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Write the syntax we just gave
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.19,0:30:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you, and then choose "image
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.21,0:30:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,literal" from the shortcut bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.84,0:30:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we're offering them the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.97,0:30:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate shortcuts in the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.18,0:30:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,bar, and then choose a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.67,0:30:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,background image.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.05,0:30:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By now, you are probably all,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.54,0:30:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,like, I know, background image,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.51,0:30:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm good, move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.94,0:30:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But, a beginner needs this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.22,0:30:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,support.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.05,0:30:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we even offer a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.10,0:30:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.77,0:30:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where you do it, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.13,0:30:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where you write the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.51,0:30:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Set background image.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.50,0:30:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at a page with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.66,0:30:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a similar goal, completing a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.38,0:30:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,task, but with a totally
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.30,0:30:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,different audience in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.03,0:30:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,These are your advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.79,0:30:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,learners.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.70,0:30:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have a goal statement,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.79,0:30:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's far more broad.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.91,0:31:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Use a breadth-first search
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.04,0:31:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,algorithm to complete the maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.63,0:31:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are any number of ways
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.08,0:31:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that I could complete this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.38,0:31:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And, I have to have a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.47,0:31:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge in my brain already to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.91,0:31:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even understand what that goal
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.32,0:31:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,statement means.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.04,0:31:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We still offer instructions, but
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.92,0:31:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,again, they're more broad, more
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.40,0:31:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,open-ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.33,0:31:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Start by adding all the tiles to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.85,0:31:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the queue.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.05,0:31:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Pop those tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.11,0:31:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.69,0:31:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in the user code
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.23,0:31:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,section, we just offer an empty
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.30,0:31:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,function and ask the user to use
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.17,0:31:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,their knowledge that they
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.62,0:31:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,already have, that we've taught
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.11,0:31:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,them a little bit of, to do
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.78,0:31:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.50,0:31:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally open-ended, overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.64,0:31:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for a beginner, but for an
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.13,0:31:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced learner, they know what
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.01,0:31:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.48,0:31:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They know how to complete this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.74,0:31:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,task, and move on with the page.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.05,0:31:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What about a different style of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.20,0:31:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,page?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.34,0:32:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking about a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.32,0:32:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In this one, we introduce Blink,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.97,0:32:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,related to Conway's Game of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.23,0:32:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Life, which is essentially a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.88,0:32:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,cell simulator, where cells live
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.70,0:32:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and die depending on how many
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.13,0:32:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,neighbors they have around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.35,0:32:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pretty complicated idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.34,0:32:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be broken down into
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.58,0:32:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,simple rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.30,0:32:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We give the learner a fair
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.82,0:32:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of text here, because
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.95,0:32:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we're introducing something
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.09,0:32:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,totally new.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.63,0:32:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And, that's part of our job, is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.67,0:32:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to explain that in detail, for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.70,0:32:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,those who are interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.03,0:32:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We do have a goal statement, but
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.13,0:32:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's embedded, and the goal is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.56,0:32:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,just to really understand these
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.19,0:32:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,algorithms, to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.77,0:32:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no clear end point, no
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.42,0:32:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,time where the page tells you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.89,0:32:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're ready to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.30,0:32:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you, to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.16,0:32:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,this, play around with the live
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.78,0:32:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,view, which you'll see in a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.52,0:32:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.83,0:32:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And, understand when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.96,0:32:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,ready, as the learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.42,0:32:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We still offer this sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.12,0:32:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,tl;dr version in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.03,0:32:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't want to read all
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.21,0:33:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that prose at the top, here are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.02,0:33:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the rules of the simulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.57,0:33:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can kind of get where you're
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.55,0:33:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,going with these.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.02,0:33:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's somewhat similar
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.03,0:33:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,structure to completing a task,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.91,0:33:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but a totally different learner
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.43,0:33:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,goal, and author goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.62,0:33:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, finally, we have, kind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.89,0:33:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of instructions, at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.93,0:33:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They're embedded, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.51,0:33:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiment with stepping through
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.35,0:33:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the simulation, which we've
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.75,0:33:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,provided on the live view side.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.77,0:33:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Try it out, and then when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.71,0:33:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ready, go on to the next page to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.66,0:33:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,explore what you'll be doing
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.80,0:33:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.93,0:33:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the audience of this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.99,0:33:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,page?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.72,0:33:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it advanced?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.12,0:33:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginner? Are they science
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.33,0:33:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,students?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.21,0:33:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they artists?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.09,0:33:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you're going to figure
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.87,0:33:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that out is, you have your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.33,0:33:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,target audience in mind, and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.05,0:33:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,then you need to do user
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.54,0:33:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.65,0:33:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Find out if this is too
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.99,0:33:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.58,0:33:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Figure out what words need to be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.95,0:33:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,defined, what concepts need to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.90,0:33:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,be explained more, or perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.77,0:33:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,less.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.67,0:33:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't underestimate your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.71,0:33:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,audience either.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.80,0:34:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it coding time yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.46,0:34:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got all these ideas, we
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.37,0:34:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,understand the goal, the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.38,0:34:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.61,0:34:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We know all the parts of the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.48,0:34:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,playground page, backward and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.90,0:34:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.91,0:34:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, it must be coding time
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.71,0:34:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.71,0:34:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet. I've moved from my
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.91,0:34:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,little notebook to my
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.44,0:34:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,whiteboard, but that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.15,0:34:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have expanded my ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.60,0:34:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.98,0:34:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some prose written down,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.61,0:34:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the coding section, I
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.48,0:34:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have transitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.34,0:34:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, in this format, I can talk
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.26,0:34:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to some of my co-workers in the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.81,0:34:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,office.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.56,0:34:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Alex, does this make any
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.05,0:34:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sense to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.63,0:34:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.65,0:34:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a cool idea, Bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.88,0:34:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Would your kids like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.84,0:34:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really important to get
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.94,0:34:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback from your actual users,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.43,0:34:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and from your colleagues, your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.71,0:34:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.65,0:34:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your prototyping phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.09,0:34:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to figure out what works and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.85,0:34:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.44,0:35:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, no, it is not coding time
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.89,0:35:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.80,0:35:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've talked through goal
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.34,0:35:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and audience, and it's time to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.13,0:35:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.40,0:35:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Passion is so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.59,0:35:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This should be threaded
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.56,0:35:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all your other
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.74,0:35:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,playground prototyping and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.14,0:35:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.49,0:35:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you even doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.65,0:35:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you writing a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.51,0:35:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,playground?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.77,0:35:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're passionate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.98,0:35:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about something that you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.08,0:35:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,share, that you want to teach to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.68,0:35:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.75,0:35:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not passionate about
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.95,0:35:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're writing a playground
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.03,0:35:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about, why are you doing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.40,0:35:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And that, that not passion is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.97,0:35:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,going to show through, and your
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.41,0:35:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,learner's not care either.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.43,0:35:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, bringing your passion to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.70,0:35:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this is so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.75,0:35:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.60,0:35:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.44,0:35:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,live view.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.57,0:35:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I said this before, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.16,0:35:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where the learner is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.66,0:35:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,get to experience their code
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.59,0:35:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,running.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.58,0:35:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where they're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.69,0:36:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,get excited about creating,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.20,0:36:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about what they've made.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.03,0:36:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is your chance to make
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.41,0:36:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience as visually
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.06,0:36:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting, as auditorily
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.03,0:36:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting, as exciting period,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.01,0:36:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for your users.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.82,0:36:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Learn to Code, where we
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.11,0:36:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,have this adorable character,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.70,0:36:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,this cool, game-style world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.17,0:36:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This appeals to a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.46,0:36:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Gets them excited about jumping
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.90,0:36:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,into this world and writing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.87,0:36:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.05,0:36:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another example of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.36,0:36:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,spirals.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.76,0:36:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I had so much fun working on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.03,0:36:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this, I would get totally
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.20,0:36:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,distracted trying to de-bug by
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.10,0:36:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,just creating cool new spirals
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.91,0:36:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and modifying variables.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.80,0:36:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.01,0:36:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you enjoy going through the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.22,0:36:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,tasks in your playground book,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.43,0:36:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your learners probably will too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.96,0:36:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And, on the other hand, if
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.08,0:36:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you're bored by the exercises,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.02,0:36:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,if you wonder why you're
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.99,0:36:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching this, how are you going
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.11,0:36:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to get your learner motivated to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.32,0:36:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,go through them either?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.71,0:36:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be excited about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.16,0:36:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing, to bring your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.70,0:36:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,passion to those views.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.39,0:37:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another cool example,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.89,0:37:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,totally different style.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.54,0:37:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, Blink.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.20,0:37:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,From that page of text you saw
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.67,0:37:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.92,0:37:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have all that text, but we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.08,0:37:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,also have this rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.40,0:37:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive, live view on the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.36,0:37:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,right hand side, where the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.86,0:37:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,learner can play with the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.69,0:37:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,algorithm, they can use touch
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.14,0:37:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,gestures to interact with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.49,0:37:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the place where passion
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.39,0:37:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can really shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.94,0:37:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So. We have the marriage of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.00,0:37:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching that Bill talked to you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.75,0:37:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about, and designing that I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.36,0:37:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,talked to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.03,0:37:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so important to keep these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.19,0:37:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind, the teaching aspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.71,0:37:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're trying to get
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.54,0:37:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,across, and how you're designing
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.19,0:37:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.59,0:37:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How you're prototyping it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.02,0:37:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Who you're talking to for help,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.58,0:37:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,how often you're user testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.75,0:37:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With these two-- when these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.03,0:37:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,powers combine, we are Captain
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.35,0:37:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.92,0:38:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So. Get ready for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.80,0:38:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Coding time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.52,0:38:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.97,0:38:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you have your prototype, or
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.90,0:38:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,excuse me, storyboard figured
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.55,0:38:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.88,0:38:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've solicited feedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.92,0:38:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,talked to your users, talked to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.85,0:38:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,whoever wanted you to make this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.07,0:38:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,playground in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.18,0:38:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.42,0:38:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotten all those things
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.54,0:38:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,together, you know what you want
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.00,0:38:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,your hints to be, you know what
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.57,0:38:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you want your success messages
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.78,0:38:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to be, how you're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.80,0:38:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,assist your learner in all the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.00,0:38:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,best ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.82,0:38:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a storyboard, now it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.95,0:38:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is time for you to write code,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.31,0:38:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and make that awesome playground
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.94,0:38:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,idea a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.99,0:38:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you don't need me to teach
